SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DIAMOND BAR; 
CITY MANAGER PAY RAISE 
The City Council on Tuesday night gave City Manager Robert Van Nort a 
$700-a-month raise and doubled his severance pay agreement. 
By a 3-1 vote with Councilwoman Phyllis Papen opposed and Councilman Paul 
Horcher absent, the council voted to increase Van Nort's annual salary from 
$80,400 to $88,800. His severance pay is eight months' salary, up from four 
months under his previous contract, which expires June 1. 
The contract also includes a $400-a-month retirement benefit. 
